  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "steve-schoger",
    "senderColor": "purple",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Reconfirming design approval, no changes",
    "content": "Already reviewed all three files earlier in this session. My approval stands -- no changes to my assessment.\n\nOn the `toHaveClass(/visually-hidden/)` tradeoff: it is slightly more implementation-specific than `not.toBeVisible()` would have been, but given Playwright's behavior with clip-path elements, it's the right call. The `.visually-hidden` class is a deliberate, well-established design pattern in our system -- it's not an incidental implementation detail. If we ever changed how we visually hide these elements, we'd want the test to flag that so we can verify the new approach still works. So the coupling here is appropriate.\n\nConsensus: approved from design. No blockers."
  }
}
